### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

When migrating code to use signals, we have situations where we need to ultimately provide an Observable of an HTTP request *and not have anything initially emitted*.

For example, if we have: 
```typescript
class Service {
    readonly theResource = resource({
        loader: () => firstValueFrom(legacyService.httpClientGetReturningObservable()),
    });
}

class Component {
    data = toObservable(this.service.theResource().value);

    constructor(private service: Service) {}
}
```
and `data` is used in our case to pass an Observable to a component such as AgGrid which will show "loading..." until the first data triggers `next(responseData)`.

Using `toObservable()` is currently exists means we get `undefined` emitted which breaks existing code.



### Proposed solution

A utility function along the lines of this adaptation of `toObservable()`

```typescript

function resourceToObservable<T>(source: Resource<T>) {
    const injector = inject(Injector);
    const subject = new ReplaySubject(1);
    const watcher = effect(
        () => {
            if (source.hasValue()) {
                let value: Exclude<T, undefined>;
                try {
                    value = source.value();
                } catch (err) {
                    untracked(() => subject.error(err));
                    return;
                }
                untracked(() => subject.next(value));
            }
        },
        {
            injector,
            manualCleanup: true,
        }
    );
    injector.get(DestroyRef).onDestroy(() => {
        watcher.destroy();
        subject.complete();
    });
    return subject.asObservable();
}
```

